channel.title: Whats happened? :( help please
channel.description:
ok so i have had my server up for a couple of days and its worked fine, im using utorrent to portfoward, basically i turned my computer off, turned it back on one day and opened no-ip and utorrent, went to run my server and it appears with the message "server is already in use."
why wont it run? :S any ideas?... my MSN is morgan_92@hotmail.com
I DO HAVE TEAM VIEWER IF THAT HELPS...
READ 3RD POST
thanks in advance.... djmorgan92

item.title: Whats happened? :( help please
item.dc:creator: @Efilite Efilite
item.description:
@Efilite wrote:

[quote=“djmorgan92, post:3, topic:280343”]did “exit” on utorrent so its not running… clicked run server and it sez my servers online… loaded my client… tried to log in and got the message “error connecting to server” … went into my GUI files and changed d33jscape.no-ip.biz (which is my servers ip) to 127.0.0.1 and i can log in now but i dont know if any1 else can :S… any1 wana add my msn and test for me???

thanks[/quote]
Yes, because you have not port forwarded and you are using the program to open the port for you. This way when you exit the program the port closes back down.

Do as I said before, uninstall and reinstall the program.

item.title: Whats happened? :( help please
item.dc:creator: @Efilite Efilite
item.description:
@Efilite wrote:

The port 43594 is in use, tihs can be caused by another program that uses the port 43594, as you are using Utorrent this may be the case.
Uninstall the program “Utorrent” and start the server again, if you do not get this problem then you obiously know that utorrent is the program effecting the ports.

If all goes well restart your computer and download + install Utorrent again.
